edu.internet2.middleware.grouperClientExt.org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods

Class OptionsMethod

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.internet2.middleware.grouperClientExt.org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodBase
      • edu.internet2.middleware.grouperClientExt.org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.OptionsMethod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HttpMethod

    public class OptionsMethod
extends HttpMethodBase
    Implements the HTTP OPTIONS method.

    The HTTP OPTIONS method is defined in section 9.2 of RFC2616:

    The OPTIONS method represents a request for information about the communication options available on the request/response chain identified by the Request-URI. This method allows the client to determine the options and/or requirements associated with a resource, or the capabilities of a server, without implying a resource action or initiating a resource retrieval.

    Since:
    1.0
